OL,3,CJustice Secretary to set out reforms
OL,4,Cto tackle 'courts emergency'
OL,6,FHe also called for judge-only trials
OL,7,Fto be used in serious and complex
OL,8,Ffraud cases, or other complex cases
OL,9,Fdetermined by a judge.
OL,11,FIn an interview with The Times, Mr
OL,12,FLammy insisted he was not preparing to
OL,13,Fannounce the "scrapping" of jury
OL,14,Ftrials.
OL,16,FBut suggested he would back Sir
OL,17,FBrian's proposals to limit them to
OL,18,Findictable-only offences, arguing that
OL,19,Fmany defendants were "playing the
OL,20,Fsystem" by delaying guilty pleas in
OL,21,Feither-way cases to the last minute.
